      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "FDA generic pump hemolysis benchmark comparison",
      "description": "CFD hemolysis index predictions compared against FDA generic centrifugal pump experimental dataset at 5 operating points. Normalized index error ranged 18–42%. Monte Carlo UQ campaign (n=2000 samples) was executed to propagate inlet boundary condition and viscosity uncertainties; sensitivity rankings from the UQ campaign identified shear-stress model coefficient as dominant contributor. Despite UQ execution, structured sensitivity analysis artefact was not registered as a linked evidence node in this assessment package."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/mesh-convergence-study",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence and GCI study for impeller passage",
      "description": "Three-level mesh refinement study on impeller passage geometry. Grid convergence index computed per Celik et al. 2008. Fine-grid GCI for hemolysis-relevant shear stress quantity: 6.3%. Achieved discretization error credibility gradation assessed as 2 against required gradation 4."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/code-verification",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Method of manufactured solutions code verification",
      "description": "MMS verification performed for laminar Navier–Stokes solver kernel. Observed order of accuracy 1.87 vs. formal order 2.0. Turbulence model implementation not independently verified. Numerical code verification credibility gradation achieved: 2; required: 4."
    }
  ],
